This Privacy Policy explains how the mobile application Mobil Cüzdan – Income & Expense Tracker (com.yatirimparadefteri.app), published on Google Play, collects, uses, and protects your personal data. By using the app, you agree to this Privacy Policy.

1. Data We Collect

Account information (optional): Email address, user ID, and display name are processed through Firebase Authentication when you sign in with email/password or Google.

Financial records: Income, expenses, transfers, amounts, dates, descriptions, categories, and custom column data that you enter. If you are signed in, this data may be stored in Google Firebase Firestore for cloud sync; otherwise it may be kept locally on your device.

Local data: Preferences and table settings may be stored on your device (for example, local storage or shared preferences).

Advertising data: The app displays Google AdMob banner ads. Google and its partners may collect advertising ID, device information, and usage data. Details are available in the Google Privacy Policy at https://policies.google.com/privacy.

Currency / gold rates: For the currency converter feature, your requests may be sent to third-party API providers (for example, exchangerate-api.com, collectapi.com) to fetch rates. Only technical connection information is sent; your account and financial records are not shared with these APIs.

2. How We Use Your Data

We use your data to provide app features (records, reports, PDF export, sync); to create accounts, enable sign-in, and back up your data; to show advertisements in the free version; for security, troubleshooting, and service improvement; and to comply with legal obligations.

3. Third Parties

Your data may be shared with or processed by the following service providers: Google Firebase (Authentication, Firestore database), Google AdMob (advertising), Google Sign-In (optional sign-in), and currency / exchange-rate API providers (rate queries only). These providers are subject to their own privacy policies.

4. Data Retention

Cloud data is retained until you delete your account or request deletion. Local data on your device may be deleted when you uninstall the app or clear the app data.

5. Your Rights (KVKK / GDPR)

Depending on your country of residence, you may have the right to access and correct your data, request deletion, object to processing (within legal limits), and request data portability.

To exercise these rights, email seheraydin4241@gmail.com. For account deletion, you may sign out in the app and send a deletion request by email; your Firestore and Authentication records will be deleted within a reasonable time.

6. Children

The app is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children.

7. Security

We take reasonable technical and administrative measures to protect your data; however, no internet or electronic storage system is 100% secure.

8. Changes

We may update this policy. For material changes, the “Last updated” date will be revised. Continued use of the app means you accept the updated policy.

